Description: A circular jar-cover of red siltware pottery, the surface covered with remains of a pale cream slip. The level of the convex top is irregular. The red fabric has inclusions of grit, particular chert and quartz particles.
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.109, p.197, pl.39)
